(All in the same Kafka consumer group)

div.div: Third party applications/clients interface with CoreNLP using HTTP and/or WebSockets. The Interface group is in charge of accepting these connections. The Interface Group is in charge of formalizing a task as requested by third party apps/clients.

div.div: Tasks are sent to the bus for actual scheduled computation. The Message Bus allows us to provide a buffer between the Interface Group, which could be demanding a high velocity of computations and the Compute Group.

div.div: In charge of actual task execution and the heavy work of computation using whatever data is available through the various datastores utilized in the system.
